    "description": "We at Neuland Laboratories Holdings Services are looking for an experienced Surgeon based out of Srinagar. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Neuland Laboratories Holdings Services:\nNeuland Laboratories Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Flexible working hours\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Srinagar, Jammu & Kashmir, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Neuland Laboratories Holdings Services!",
